data.title: General Eisenhower and his wife, Mamie deplane, Washington, D. C., 18 June 1945
data.text: Photograph. U.S. General Dwight Eisenhower and his wife, Mamie, walking down steps from an airplane. Official Caption: "Rome, 6/28/45 -- Eisenhower greets wife -- U.S. General of the Army Dwight D. Eisenhower chats with his wife on the steps of the plane that brought him from Paris to Washington June 18 on his first trip home since he led Allied Forces to victory in Europe.--International News Photo through Rome OWI--Approved by appropriate military authority (List A out) 6912." Washington, D. C. 18 June 1945
